Keep @Garlic Herb Parmesan Chicken Wings{1%unit}, @Buffalo Chicken Wings{1%unit}, and @Cajun Chicken Wings{1%unit} frozen or refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days.

If frozen, thaw in the #refrigerator{} (at 40 degrees) overnight or at room temperature for ~thaw{2-3%hours} before eating.

> The best way to celebrate Father's Day is with a cookout. Is there anything more cookout-worthy than chicken wings? The answer is no! This combo comes with three finger-licking flavors: garlic herb parmesan, spicy buffalo, and savory Cajun-style. Once baked, these wings are perfectly crispy on the outside and super juicy on the inside. The only question is whether to dip them in blue cheese or ranch!

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Place wings on a lightly oiled, foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Bake on middle rack for ~{15%minutes}.

Flip wings and cook until lightly browned and crispy, ~{10%minutes} more.